channel.title: Goodbye forever
channel.description:
I really dont have much to say.
This last summer has been incredible, I realised that life is too good to spend it on the computer. I'm not just leaving this forum, I'm leaving everywhere. Too many reasons but lets just say life has never been better. So yeah, bye. I'll be on msn sometimes for those who added me. The only computer stuff I'll be doing is at my new job in england(I am back and fourth from Canada to Britain all the time). I will be working on flash programs and I get paid A LOT. My Cousin gave me a job at his company and it's just awesome. I have a girlfriend in Britain now and life is great,
Bye!

item.title: Goodbye forever
item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

Lol thanks.

Just to clear some things up:

I’ll be on msn still. I’m basically just quitting all forums and not gonna bother with any programming other then actionscript. I realise people think I will come back but I won’t because I have lost all interest in hanging out on forums. And, the money isn’t a whole lot but it is A LOT to me because I am 15. Over the summer I’ll make about $13,000 with my cousin’s company. I do various things, actionscripting, animating, and when they need it I make 3d models because they do need a lot of graphics. It’s pretty simple but you have to work superfast. The company does a few things, they build complex programs from flash and they also make websites and host them and stuff. It’s a small business but they have a nice office and everything. Oh yeah and another thing, one thing I love about british girls is that they are not all bimbo’s. In Canada where I lived there were a lot of hotties but they were dumb as hell. In Britain they are much more intelligent(or so it seems anyways). My girlfriend lives with 4 brothers and she is very motherly and intelligent and everything I like in a girl. I’m in Canada at the moment but I’m going back to London soon. This is probably my last post here and I quit all other forums.
